section.section:
The powers granted to any official or agency pursuant to this subsection may not be construed:
To grant to the official or agency powers in any substantive area not otherwise granted to the official or agency by other public general or public local law;
To restrict the official or agency from exercising any power granted to the official or agency by other public general or public local law or otherwise;
To authorize the official or agency or officers of the agency to engage in any activity which is beyond their power under other public general law, public local law, or otherwise; or
To preempt or supersede the regulatory authority of any State department or agency under any public general law.
